## ğŸš€ How to Run
### âœ… Prerequisites

- Java JDK 17+
- Maven
- IntelliJ IDEA or any Java IDE
- Internet connection (for downloading Maven dependencies)

### ğŸ”§ Setup Steps

1. **Clone the repository**
   ```bash
   git clone https://github.com/your-username/your-repo-name.git
   cd RestAssured

2. Import the project in IntelliJ IDEA
Open IntelliJ â†’ Open Project â†’ select the folder.

3. Build project with Maven
(bash)
mvn clean install

4.Run the tests
Run tests from:
IDE using the testing.xml
Or via terminal: (bash)
mvn test


ğŸ“š Features Covered
âœ”ï¸ Basic HTTP methods (GET, POST, PUT, DELETE)
âœ”ï¸ Multiple ways of creating request body (POJO, HashMap, JSON)
âœ”ï¸ Response validation (status code, headers, body)
âœ”ï¸ Logging of requests and responses
âœ”ï¸ Query & path parameters
âœ”ï¸ Parsing JSON and XML responses
âœ”ï¸ Schema validation (JSON/XSD)
âœ”ï¸ Serialization & Deserialization
âœ”ï¸ Authentication (Basic, Digest, OAuth)
âœ”ï¸ Fake data generation using JavaFaker
âœ”ï¸ User operations with reusable methods

